Second round of excellent sales at Honda.
In November, Honda will start marketing the second generation Honda Jazz.
While its predecessor had a large interior, this people carrier offers a much larger one.
In addition, there are the technical refinements that enable even more comfortable driving and fuel savings.
Changes before the upcoming revolution.
So is the second generation of the Honda Jazz.
Although, aesthetically speaking, the new Jazz shares a similar line to its predecessor, the changes made to this large sedan are numerous.
Among other things, the innovative design, the new spatial flexibility, the larger dimensions of the car and the new mechanics should be emphasized.
However, before starting to analyze the new model, it must be said that this new Jazz appears six years later, after the first generation appeared on the market.
According to the first observations, compared to other manufacturers, Honda managed to update this model for a shorter period of time.
Although the Honda Jazz is less known in Europe, this model is a phenomenon in terms of its sales in other markets.
This is a case in Japan, the country where the Jazz is the best-selling car of 2002 and throughout 2008.
After the Jazz appeared on the market, around a million models were sold in Japan alone.
The second market was the Old Continent, with around half a million cars sold in six years.
Despite this, Honda is trying to increase sales of the new Jazz model within the segment.
Thus, while Japanese company sold a total of 83,000 Jazz models in 2007, the expected estimates are 10,000 cars. That is 17% of the assumed growth on the European market.
As for the Spanish market, Honda has sold a total of 8,000 Jazz models since 2002. That is 6.7% of the total sales at Honda in Spain.
As for the new generation of the model, the managers of the Spanish branch expect to be able to sell 2,000 Jazz models a year.
In more detail, the appearance of the new Honda Jazz model makes it possible to cover up the drop in sales in Spain.
In reality, the brand&#39;s leaders hope to close the year with total sales of 22,000 models. That&#39;s 4,000 fewer cars than in 2007, a drop of 16%.
Despite this increase in sales, Honda has increased its market share in Spain to 1.8% compared to last year (1.6%).
At the same time, the Japanese company hopes to reach 2% in 2010.
To achieve this share, Honda is betting on the appearance of a new model.
It&#39;s Insight, a 5-door hybrid car with a compact size of 4.7 meters in length, the Japanese company hopes to sell around 200,000 models a year around the world.
According to the Japanese manufacturer&#39;s market estimates, 50% of Insight models are sold in the United States, while the remaining share is distributed in the Old Continent and Japan.
The Insight&#39;s market launch is scheduled for the first months of the year, for the first time its public presentation will take place in January in Valencia.
With regard to the first generation, the new Jazz grows in all its sizes.
Its length is 3.90 meters (plus 5 centimeters), its width is 1.69 meters (plus 2 centimeters) and the distance between the axles is 2.50 meters, which leads to the assumption that it has grown 5 centimeters.
The height, on the other hand, does not change and remains 1.52 meters.
Along with the increase in dimensions, the interior space is also increased.
This success is due on the one hand to the new space flexibility program and on the other hand to the central position of the fuel tank, a solution also used on the previous Jazz model.
Also the capacity of the trunk, which has a double loading surface system, reaches up to 339 liters, that is 19 liters more than the capacity of the trunk of the first generation.
It should be emphasized that these measures are present in the version with a 1.4 liter petrol engine, because the trunk capacity of the Honda Jazz with a 1.2 liter petrol engine is 379 liters.
Among other improvements, apart from additional equipment such as leather seats or the possibility of installing panoramic windows, improved access to seats is offered.
The opening angle of the rear doors is 80 degrees, while the first Jazz had only 67 degrees.
The engines of the second generation of Jazz are also new.
At the beginning of its commercialization, this small model has 2 versions of petrol engines: 1.2 and 1.4 liters.
Both variants have i-VTEC system, which enables low fuel consumption and lower CO2 emissions, has excellent technical performance and at the same time provides high-torque performance for the entire engine running time.
The first variant with 1.2 liters achieves an output of 90 hp at 6,000 rpm with a maximum torque of 114 Nm at 4,900 rpm.
This petrol engine - the previous Jazz model achieves 78 hp - has a fuel consumption of 5.3 liters and CO2 emissions of 125 grams.
In view of the previous engine, which reached 83 hp in the previous generation, it now manages to reach 100 hp.
The Jazz 100 hp 1.4 model consumes 5.4 liters of fuel and emits 128 grams of CO2.
