On the other hand, there is now a wave of indignation at the existing leaderships, especially those of economics, which have turned out to be insufficient and full of shadow zones.
Finally, there is a deeper and, in a sense, even more troubling aspect: a loss of confidence, an intolerance, an image of impracticality, a sense of distance, all aimed at a whole class of Western managers.
The conviction seems to be paving the way among large parts of the population that it is not just the actions of the social elite, but already their world of ideas, their way of life, their culture in the broadest sense of the word, the content of which is represents the majority as more and more foreign and outdated.
