But there are also local politicians who resist the pressure of the &#39;Ndrangheta: heroes who get a clean slate.&quot;
This morning&#39;s arrests follow those of last July, which police say the Piromalli clan was beheaded.
Since the end of last April, the municipal council of Gioia Tauro had been dissolved, but already in 1991 - and even then due to alleged links between organized crime and the local administration - local politicians had been relieved of their municipal offices.
